                "text": "In 2024, the researcher’s bibliographic production (from the available Lattes data) includes **3 journal articles**, **1 book chapter**, and **1 complete conference paper**.\n\n### Most relevant (as far as the available data allows)\nThe Lattes entries do not provide an objective ranking metric for “most relevant” (e.g., journal quartile, citations in 2024, or impact factor). Therefore, **I can’t determine a definitive single “most relevant” item** from the provided information alone.\n\nHowever, among the 2024 publications, a clear highlight is a **journal article in _Future Generation Computer Systems_**:\n\n- **“MAS-Cloud+: A novel multi-agent architecture with reasoning models for resource management in multiple providers”** — *Future Generation Computer Systems*, **vol. 154**, pp. **16–34** (2024). DOI: **10.1016/j.future.2023.12.022**.\n\n### Other 2024 items recorded\n- **Journal:** “A novel GPU-based approach for embedded NARMAX/FROLS system identification” — *Mechanical Systems and Signal Processing*, vol. **211**, art. **111261** (2024). DOI: **10.1016/j.ymssp.2024.111261**.  \n- **Journal:** “Adaptive Patch Grid Strategy for Parallel Protein Folding using Atomic Burials with NAMD” — *Journal of Parallel and Distributed Computing*, vol. **189**, art. **104868** (2024). DOI: **10.1016/j.jpdc.2024.104868**.  \n- **Book chapter:** “A Supercomputação na Era da Inteligência Artificial” — *Grandes Desafios em Ciência da Computação* (2024), pp. **27–32**. DOI: **10.5753/sbc.16840.7.5**.  \n- **Conference paper:** “A Framework for Automated Parallel Execution of Scientific Multi-workflow Applications in the Cloud with Work Stealing” — *Euro-Par 2024* (2024), pp. **298–311**.\n\nIf you tell me what criterion you want for “most relevant” (e.g., **best-ranked venue**, **only journals**, **most-cited in 2024**, etc.), I can select accordingly—but with the current data, the best-supported “highlight” is the *Future Generation Computer Systems* 